cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a machine learning approach to learn heuristic algorithms for combinatorial optimization problems. This involves using reinforcement learning and graph embedding techniques to learn a policy that constructs a solution incrementally. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), as it involves learning algorithms using reinforcement learning. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) for the same reason. Additionally, since the paper deals with optimization problems over graphs, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
